You got a lip on you.
That's all right.

797
01:04:47,418 --> 01:04:50,513
I don't generally care for it,
but that's all right.

798
01:04:51,856 --> 01:04:54,791
You was a good sport to bump the shmatte.

799
01:04:55,861 --> 01:04:57,954
How do you know Mink skipped?

800
01:04:58,030 --> 01:05:00,864
- Because the Dane can't find him.
- So he says.

801
01:05:00,934 --> 01:05:05,030
- Meaning what exactly?
-Maybe nothing.

802
01:05:05,105 --> 01:05:09,167
I didn't give it much thought, 'cause
a guy'll say anything when his number is up.

803
01:05:09,243 --> 01:05:11,974
But, uh,just before I bumped Bernie,

804
01:05:12,047 --> 01:05:15,141
he swore to me that Eddie Dane
 and Mink were setting him up--

805
01:05:15,217 --> 01:05:18,153
that they were the ones who sold out your fix.

806
01:05:26,732 --> 01:05:28,666
Well, uh--

807
01:05:28,734 --> 01:05:31,066
Well, like you say, uh, a guy'll say anything.

808
01:05:31,136 --> 01:05:33,571
So why isn't Eddie Dane here?

809
01:05:35,341 --> 01:05:37,970
Well, he don't care for you, kid.

810
01:05:39,046 --> 01:05:41,982
Maybe it's only fair to tell you.

811
01:05:42,050 --> 01:05:45,542
After you left us, he tried
to sell me on a double-cross.

812
01:05:45,620 --> 01:05:48,522
He says to me, why don't we
double-cross you and give you the bump...

813
01:05:48,591 --> 01:05:50,525
after we get the shmatte.

814
01:05:50,593 --> 01:05:54,587
Well, I figure a deal's a deal.
You're square with me.

815
01:05:54,664 --> 01:05:59,398
You bump the shmatte, I hold up my end.
It's a question of ethics.

816
01:05:59,470 --> 01:06:03,771
Everything above board so everybody knows
 who's a friend, who's an enemy.

817
01:06:05,144 --> 01:06:08,342
So the Dane doesn't like you,
but he wouldn't cross me.

818
01:06:08,414 --> 01:06:10,348
