and then you'd let me go again.

929
01:15:23,574 --> 01:15:26,907
Hello, Tad.
How's the club holding up?

930
01:15:26,978 --> 01:15:30,178
We're managing to squeak by without you.
 Got Lazarre's money?

931
01:15:30,303 --> 01:15:31,106
No.

932
01:15:31,206 --> 01:15:33,408
You're not supposed to be here
 since you turned rat.

933
01:15:33,508 --> 01:15:36,222
Relax, Tad.
Leo isn't around, is he?

934
01:15:36,556 --> 01:15:40,180
Last couple of days you booked any heavy
 bets on a long shot at Saturday's fights?

935
01:15:40,336 --> 01:15:42,321
Why the hell should I tell you?

936
01:15:43,532 --> 01:15:45,897
The truth is, Tad, no reason on Earth.

937
01:15:49,000 --> 01:15:50,800
Saturday's fights?

938
01:15:51,374 --> 01:15:55,334
Drop Johnson put two grand
 on one yesterday--

939
01:15:55,412 --> 01:15:58,848
on Sailor Reese, an undercard bum.

940
01:15:58,917 --> 01:16:01,977
DropJohnson.
He play your book much?

941
01:16:02,053 --> 01:16:05,353
- Are you kidding?
 I didn't even know he could count.

942
01:16:05,424 --> 01:16:07,688
Jesus. You bring them with you?

943
01:16:07,760 --> 01:16:11,162
Hello, Brian.
Still fighting the good fight?

944
01:16:11,231 --> 01:16:13,529
Hello, Tom.
Neither rain nor wind nor snow.

945
01:16:13,600 --> 01:16:15,694
That's the mailman. O'Doole here?

946
01:16:22,177 --> 01:16:25,113
Hello, O'Doole.
You don't look happy.

947
01:16:25,181 --> 01:16:27,308
Look at this mess.

948
01:16:27,384 --> 01:16:30,684
Guttin' the golden calf again.
I don't know whether to laugh or cry.

949
01:16:30,755 --> 01:16:34,452
Yeah, it's awful confusing.
You know a yegg named DropJohnson?

950
01:16:34,525 --> 01:16:37,324
- We spanked him a couple of times.
- Where does he flop?

951
01:16:37,396 --> 01:16:39,591
- Terminal Hotel, Bay Street.

952
01:16:39,664 --> 01:16:44,068
Jesus! Look, don't nobody ask me
 since I'm just the chief around here,

953
01:16:44,137 --> 01:16:46,231
but I'll tell you my opinion.

954
01:16:46,306 --> 01:16:50,675
Caspar is just as crazy as Leo,
and an ''eye-tie'' into the bargain.

955
01:16:50,745 --> 01:16:53,908
What's the matter, O'Doole?
Doesn't anything ever suit you?

956
01:17:04,127 --> 01:17:06,926
Hop in, Tom.
We been lookin'for you.

957
01:17:06,998 --> 01:17:09,398
- I'm busy.
- Hop in anyway.

958
01:17:09,467 --> 01:17:12,733
You can't hijack me, Tic-Tac.
We're on the same side now.

959
01:17:12,805 --> 01:17:15,603
Or didn't you get that far in school?

960
01:17:24,952 --> 01:17:26,817
How'd you get the fat lip?

961
01:17:26,887 --> 01:17:31,257
- Old war wound. Acts up around morons.
- Very smart.

962
01:17:31,326 --> 01:17:34,455
What were you doing at the club,
talking things over with Leo?

963
01:17:34,530 --> 01:17:37,466
Don't think so hard, Eddie.
You might sprain something.

964
01:17:37,534 --> 01:17:40,264
You are so goddamn smart.

965
01:17:40,337 --> 01:17:42,271
Except you ain't.

966
01:17:42,339 --> 01:17:45,309
I get you, smart guy.
I know what you are.

967
01:17:45,376 --> 01:17:47,310
Straight as a corkscrew.

968
01:17:47,378 --> 01:17:49,313
Mr. Inside Out-ski,

969
01:17:49,381 --> 01:17:53,512
like some goddamn Bolshevik
 picking up his orders from Yegg Central.

970
01:17:53,587 --> 01:17:55,680
You think you're
so goddamn smart.

971
01:17:55,755 --> 01:17:57,950
You join upJohnny Caspar,

972
01:17:58,024 --> 01:18:00,118
you bump Bernie Bernbaum.

973
01:18:01,329 --> 01:18:04,731
Up is down. Black is white.

974
01:18:06,068 --> 01:18:09,129
Well, I think you're half smart.

975
01:18:09,205 --> 01:18:11,799
I think you were straight with your frail,

976
01:18:11,875 --> 01:18:14,470
I think you were queer with Johnny Caspar...

977
01:18:14,545 --> 01:18:18,743
and I think you'd sooner join
a ladies' league than gun a guy down.

978
01:18:18,816 --> 01:18:23,220
Then I hear from these two geniuses
 they never even saw this rub-out take place.

979
01:18:23,288 --> 01:18:24,934
Boss said to have him do it.
He didn't say nothing about--

980
01:18:25,034 --> 01:18:25,898
 Shut up!

981
01:18:27,226 --> 01:18:30,390
Or maybe you still got too many teeth.

982
01:18:32,999 --> 01:18:37,198
Everyone is so goddamn smart.

983
01:18:37,271 --> 01:18:41,038
Well, we'll go out to Miller's Crossing...

984
01:18:41,110 --> 01:18:44,045
and we'll see who's smart.

985
01:19:08,208 --> 01:19:12,407
You understand if we don't find
a stiff out here, we leave a fresh one.

986
01:19:29,433 --> 01:19:32,369
Where are your friends when you need 'em, huh?

987
01:19:33,605 --> 01:19:36,039
Where's Leo now?

988
01:19:38,011 --> 01:19:40,445
Hey, Tic-Tac!

989
01:19:40,513 --> 01:19:44,348
You ever notice
 how the snappy dialogue dries up...

990
01:19:44,418 --> 01:19:46,978
once a guy starts soiling his union suit?

991
01:20:30,740 --> 01:20:35,007
Okay. There's nothing out here.

992
01:20:48,060 --> 01:20:52,862
- Think about this... smart guy.

993
01:20:52,933 --> 01:20:55,835
It's hanky time.

994
01:21:00,609 --> 01:21:03,942
- Birds have been at him.

995
01:21:04,013 --> 01:21:06,505
Jesus Christ.

996
01:21:31,146 --> 01:21:35,082
Told you to put one in his brain,
not in his stinkin' face!

997
01:21:39,088 --> 01:21:42,820
I told you, Dane.
We heard two shots.

998
01:22:10,392 --> 01:22:12,486
Hello, Drop.

999
01:22:16,199 --> 01:22:18,634
How are the Katzenjammers?

1000
01:22:18,702 --> 01:22:21,432
Hello, Tom. What's the rumpus?

1001
01:22:22,807 --> 01:22:25,002
Had any visitors?

1002
01:22:25,076 --> 01:22:27,169
Uhh, no.

1003
01:22:27,245 --> 01:22:29,180
Not ever, Drop?

1004
01:22:29,248 --> 01:22:31,239
Not lately.

1005
01:22:31,317 --> 01:22:33,878
Then you must be happy to see me.

1006
01:22:37,023 --> 01:22:38,958
So, uh...

1007
01:22:39,026 --> 01:22:42,894
you didn't see Bernie Bernbaum
before he was shown across.

1008
01:22:42,964 --> 01:22:44,990
Uh, no.

1009
01:22:45,067 --> 01:22:47,126
Seen him since?

1010
01:22:49,239 --> 01:22:51,571
One last question, Drop.

1011
01:22:51,641 --> 01:22:56,238
You got a lot of money on tomorrow's fight.

1012
01:22:56,313 --> 01:23:00,478
That your bet, or, uh...
you placing it for a friend?

1013
01:23:00,552 --> 01:23:02,486
No, no, no, it's my bet.

1014
01:23:02,554 --> 01:23:07,254
- I just have a good feeling about that fight.
- A good feeling, huh?

1015
01:23:07,326 --> 01:23:09,955
When did a feeling return to your head?

1016
01:23:10,030 --> 01:23:12,658
You've outgrown that one.

1017
01:23:12,733 --> 01:23:14,929
Must be all the thinking you been doing.

1018
01:23:15,003 --> 01:23:18,097
Tell Bernie something's come up,
he has to get in touch.

1019
01:23:18,173 --> 01:23:21,166
There'll be nothing stirring
 till I talk to him.

1020
01:23:53,515 --> 01:23:58,749
All right, anyone left in there,
come on out grabbing air. You know the drill.

1021
01:24:14,540 --> 01:24:17,305
Aah!

1022
01:25:00,061 --> 01:25:02,996
Hello, Tom.
Where you been hiding?

1023
01:25:03,064 --> 01:25:05,329
Hither and yon.
Is the mayor in?

1024
01:25:05,401 --> 01:25:07,892
- He's with Mr. Caspar.
- That's who I'm looking for.

1025
01:25:07,970 --> 01:25:11,168
- Scare me up some gargle, will you?
- Sure. I'll announce you.

1026
01:25:11,241 --> 01:25:14,006
Don't bother. I'm well-liked.

1027
01:25:18,917 --> 01:25:21,909
-Assistants, maybe.
- For a mayor, you don't hear so hot.

1028
01:25:21,987 --> 01:25:25,014
I said head.
Head of the assessor's office.

1029
01:25:25,091 --> 01:25:29,256
- But there are two of them.
- I can count. Co-heads.

1030
01:25:29,330 --> 01:25:32,424
Johnny, needless to say,
this office will do anything in its power...

1031
01:25:32,499 --> 01:25:35,094
to assist you and your cousins.

1032
01:25:35,170 --> 01:25:38,390
We did it for Leo, of course,
on countless occasions.

1033
01:25:38,490 --> 01:25:42,833
Damn right. Had every potato-eater
from County Cork on the public tit.

1034
01:25:42,911 --> 01:25:45,346
But there's a way we do things,

1035
01:25:45,414 --> 01:25:47,501
hallowed by usage and consecrated by time.

1036
01:25:48,053 --> 01:25:51,855
When we put people on the pad
when Leo was running things--

1037
01:25:51,955 --> 01:25:53,405
Leo ain't runnin' things!

1038
01:25:53,791 --> 01:25:58,195
I ain't interested in ancient history!
I'm runnin'things now!

1039
01:25:58,263 --> 01:26:00,755
Nobody can appreciate it more than I.

1040
01:26:00,833 --> 01:26:03,131
I can give them jobs.
I can give them good jobs.

1041
01:26:03,202 --> 01:26:06,366
I can even give them jobs where
 they won't have to perform any work,

1042
01:26:06,439 --> 01:26:09,272
where their lack of English
 will be no impediment, but I can't--

1043
01:26:09,342 --> 01:26:11,607
What is this, the high hat?

1044
01:26:11,679 --> 01:26:16,913
Tom, can you explain it to him?
 I can put them in public works, but I can't--

1045
01:26:16,985 --> 01:26:18,919
You can do whatever the hell
Caspar tells you.

1046
01:26:18,987 --> 01:26:21,456
I don't remember all this double talk
when Leo gave you an order.

1047
01:26:21,524 --> 01:26:25,790
- Tom, Jesus!
- Stop whimpering and do as you're told.

1048
01:26:25,862 --> 01:26:29,060
- You can start by gettin'out of here.
 -Johnny, it's my office.

1049
01:26:29,133 --> 01:26:34,128
Get out of here! Take it on the heel
 and toe before I whack you one!

1050
01:26:36,374 --> 01:26:38,775
- You two beat it.

1051
01:26:38,845 --> 01:26:42,976
- Yeah, go and keep the mayor company.

1052
01:26:43,050 --> 01:26:46,110
I'll take care
of ya's later.

1053
01:26:55,598 --> 01:26:58,534
- Runnin' things--
it ain't all gravy.

1054
01:26:58,602 --> 01:27:02,733
- What's the fireworks?
-Knocking over one of Leo's clubs.

1055
01:27:02,807 --> 01:27:05,935
Son of a bitch won't go belly up.

1056
01:27:06,010 --> 01:27:09,139
I'm sorry, kid.
I heard about your little ride this morning.

1057
01:27:09,214 --> 01:27:11,148
Yeah, well, sorry don't fix things.

1058
01:27:11,216 --> 01:27:15,051
We could just as easily have missed
 Bernie's corpse, and I'd be dead now.

1059
01:27:15,121 --> 01:27:18,888
I know, I know, but that don't mean
 the Dane's up to anything.

1060
01:27:18,959 --> 01:27:22,793
So he hears a rumor that Bernie ain't dead.
 These stories pop up.

1061
01:27:22,863 --> 01:27:26,095
Any stories about Bernie being alive
the Dane's made up himself.

1062
01:27:26,167 --> 01:27:30,036
You don't know that.
 It don't make sense. Why would he?

1063
01:27:30,106 --> 01:27:32,540
There could be a damn good reason...

1064
01:27:34,278 --> 01:27:37,111
if you got a fixed fight coming up.

1065
01:27:39,417 --> 01:27:42,511
- Do you?
- Maybe.

1066
01:27:44,189 --> 01:27:48,216
Okay, yeah, sure. Tomorrow night.
The fix is in. What of it?

1067
01:27:48,294 --> 01:27:50,559
- The Dane know about it?
- Yeah.

1068
01:27:54,435 --> 01:27:57,029
Okay, I get it.

1069
01:27:57,104 --> 01:27:59,707
If the Dane's been selling you out
on these fights and means to again,

1070
01:27:59,807 --> 01:28:01,788
 he's gonna have to have somebody else
 to point the finger at.

1071
01:28:01,888 --> 01:28:02,809
 Yeah, I get it.

1072
01:28:03,345 --> 01:28:05,780
With Bernie dead, there ain't a hell
of a lot of people he can point to.

1073
01:28:05,848 --> 01:28:09,614
Yeah, the Dane sells me out,
makes pretend Bernie's still doing it.

1074
01:28:09,686 --> 01:28:11,621
That's real pretty.

1075
01:28:11,689 --> 01:28:15,786
Bernie leaked the fix,
and you take the fall for not killing him.

1076
01:28:17,896 --> 01:28:22,334
But I don't know.
Why would Eddie cross me like that? Money?

1077
01:28:22,401 --> 01:28:24,631
Okay, everybody likes money,

1078
01:28:24,704 --> 01:28:27,902
but somehow it just don't seem like him.

1079
01:28:27,975 --> 01:28:32,504
- And I know the Dane.
- Nobody knows anybody. Not that well.

1080
01:28:32,580 --> 01:28:35,310
Money don't mean that much to him.

1081
01:28:35,383 --> 01:28:37,614
Then it's not just the money he's after.

1082
01:28:37,686 --> 01:28:41,418
- He's got a wart on his fanny.
- Huh?

1083
01:28:41,491 --> 01:28:45,052
A wart on his fanny giving him the fidgets.

1084
01:28:45,128 --> 01:28:47,563
Maybe he's sick of sitting on the couch.

1085
01:28:47,631 --> 01:28:50,794
Maybe behind your desk don't look
 like a bad place to move to.

1086
01:28:50,868 --> 01:28:53,337
Kid, you got a lip on you.

1087
01:28:54,639 --> 01:28:57,040
But you're honest.

1088
01:28:57,110 --> 01:29:00,705
That's something we can't get enough of
 in this business.

1089
01:29:04,251 --> 01:29:07,710
I'll admit since last we jawed...

1090
01:29:07,789 --> 01:29:10,189
my stomach's been seizing up on me.

1091
01:29:10,258 --> 01:29:13,228
If the Dane's saying
we should double-cross you--

1092
01:29:13,295 --> 01:29:17,562
You double-cross once, where's it all end?

1093
01:29:17,634 --> 01:29:20,432
An interesting ethical question.

1094
01:29:25,877 --> 01:29:29,109
I'll find the Dane, talk to him,
straighten things out.

1095
01:29:29,181 --> 01:29:31,778
- Sure, talk to him. Have a chat.
 - I'll take care of it.

1096
01:29:31,878 --> 01:29:33,941
- Ask him if he's selling you out.
I'm sure he'll come clean.

1097
01:29:34,385 --> 01:29:35,621
I'll take care of it.

1098
01:29:35,755 --> 01:29:37,975
- You're swimmin' in it.
- I said I'd take care of it!

1099
01:29:48,905 --> 01:29:52,432
-Johnny.

1100
01:29:52,508 --> 01:29:56,843
My chin's hanging out right alongside yours.

1101
01:29:58,482 --> 01:30:01,919
I'd worry a lot less if I thought
 you were worrying enough.

1102
01:30:06,392 --> 01:30:08,326
But I am, kid.

1103
01:30:12,065 --> 01:30:13,999
Christ.

1104
01:30:15,236 --> 01:30:17,636
Running things.

1105
01:30:27,917 --> 01:30:30,318
- Yeah? I got your message.

1106
01:30:30,387 --> 01:30:33,550
Oh, Bernie.
 I had a dream about you the other day.

1107
01:30:33,624 --> 01:30:37,152
- Yeah? A nightmare?
- On the contrary. Very sweet.

1108
01:30:37,229 --> 01:30:40,427
I dreamt you were lying out
at Miller's Crossing with your face blown off.

1109
01:30:40,500 --> 01:30:43,992
You get a kick out of that?
- I was in stitches.

1110
01:30:44,070 --> 01:30:46,938
- It's Mink, isn't it?
 - I came back. He wasn't happy to see me.

1111
01:30:47,007 --> 01:30:48,941
- Can you beat that?
- Some friend.

1112
01:30:49,009 --> 01:30:50,944
Yeah. You know what a nervous boy he was.

1113
01:30:51,012 --> 01:30:54,846
I figured you're a friend,
 maybe you could use some insurance.

1114
01:30:54,916 --> 01:30:56,885
Did Mink have a .22?

1115
01:30:58,954 --> 01:31:01,981
-He already ditched it. Why?
- After he shot Rug?

1116
01:31:02,058 --> 01:31:05,221
- Yeah. How'd you know?
- Doesn't matter.

1117
01:31:05,295 --> 01:31:10,029
I've been thinking about our deal.
You can stick it in your ear.

1118
01:31:10,101 --> 01:31:13,538
You don't have anything on me that I don't
 have on you, so I'm calling your bluff.

1119
01:31:13,605 --> 01:31:15,869
- Wait a minute.
- I'm pulling out tomorrow morning.

1120
01:31:15,941 --> 01:31:19,571
You only have to decide whether or not
 I leave behind a message for Caspar...

1121
01:31:19,646 --> 01:31:21,580
that you're still around.

1122
01:31:21,648 --> 01:31:24,083
If you want me to keep my mouth shut,
 it's gonna cost you some dough.

1123
01:31:24,151 --> 01:31:26,711
I figure a thousand bucks is reasonable,
so I want two.

1124
01:31:26,787 --> 01:31:30,019
- In a pig's eye! - I'm going out.
I'll be back at 4:00 this morning.

1125
01:31:30,091 --> 01:31:33,027
If you're not here at my place, 4:00,
with the dough,

1126
01:31:33,095 --> 01:31:36,394
- Caspar's gonna be looking for you tomorrow.
- Wait, wait, wait!

1127
01:31:44,275 --> 01:31:47,733
- Got any money?
- No.

1128
01:31:49,114 --> 01:31:51,446
Okay.

1129
01:32:05,767 --> 01:32:07,701
Third race tonight.

1130
01:32:07,769 --> 01:32:11,570
By the finish,
Tailor Made had a view of the field.

1131
01:32:11,641 --> 01:32:14,133
You oughta lay off the ponies, Tom.

1132
01:32:20,752 --> 01:32:22,686
Okay.

1133
01:32:28,928 --> 01:32:32,490
Lazarre said he's sorry about this.
 It's just getting out of hand.

1134
01:32:32,566 --> 01:32:34,501
Yeah.

1135
01:32:34,569 --> 01:32:36,503
He likes you, Tom.

1136
01:32:36,571 --> 01:32:39,107
He said we didn't have to break anything.

1137
01:32:39,942 --> 01:32:42,103
It's okay.

1138
01:32:42,177 --> 01:32:44,771
Tell him there's no hard feelings. Heh!

1139
01:32:44,848 --> 01:32:49,012
Christ, Tom... he knows that.

1140
01:32:51,622 --> 01:32:53,783
Take care now.

1141
01:33:08,108 --> 01:33:10,076
- Tom Reagan.
- Yes, sir.

1142
01:33:10,144 --> 01:33:13,740
- Mr. Caspar's in the great room.
- Swell. Can you hold these?

1143
01:33:15,283 --> 01:33:17,309
Kid, what's the rumpus?

1144
01:33:17,386 --> 01:33:19,320
I got news.

1145
01:33:19,388 --> 01:33:22,552
Yeah. News at this end too.

1146
01:33:22,626 --> 01:33:25,060
My stomach's been seizing up on me.

1147
01:33:25,128 --> 01:33:27,825
- Mink just told me that he--
- Eh?

1148
01:33:27,899 --> 01:33:31,426
- You talked to Mink?
- Yeah, on the phone.

1149
01:33:31,503 --> 01:33:34,631
The Dane wants you to think that he's
 disappeared so you can't talk to him,

1150
01:33:34,706 --> 01:33:37,767
- but he's been here in town.
- You sure it was Mink?

1151
01:33:37,844 --> 01:33:41,678
Yeah. See for yourself.
He's coming to my place, 4:00 this morning.

1152
01:33:41,748 --> 01:33:45,549
He's afraid of a crossing with Dane.
 He told me about the fix.

1153
01:33:45,619 --> 01:33:49,021
He says he'll sing for a couple of grand
 skip money, tell us everyone involved.

1154
01:33:49,090 --> 01:33:51,524
But you'd better take care of the Dane tonight.

1155
01:33:51,593 --> 01:33:54,461
Mink says he's coming after us tonight.

1156
01:34:00,437 --> 01:34:02,998
Leo's holed up at Whiskey Nick's dump.

1157
01:34:03,074 --> 01:34:05,008
What? How do you know?

1158
01:34:05,076 --> 01:34:08,205
That ain't all we know, smart guy.

1159
01:34:09,281 --> 01:34:12,580
Recognize your playmate?

1160
01:34:16,656 --> 01:34:19,490
You thought I'd quit, huh? Uh-uh.

1161
01:34:19,560 --> 01:34:22,495
I followed you this afternoon,

1162
01:34:22,563 --> 01:34:26,193
and I wondered why Einstein
would wanna talk to a gorilla.

1163
01:34:26,268 --> 01:34:29,796
So I grabbed the gorilla,
 and I beat it out of him.

1164
01:34:29,872 --> 01:34:33,467
You give me a big guy every time.
They break easy. Not like you.

1165
01:34:33,543 --> 01:34:36,980
Is there a point, or are you just brushing up
on your small talk?

1166
01:34:37,047 --> 01:34:40,540
I like that. Cool under fire.

1167
01:34:41,620 --> 01:34:43,588
I'm impressed.

1168
01:34:45,258 --> 01:34:48,921
The gorilla didn't know whose stiff
we found, but I can fill that in.

1169
01:34:48,995 --> 01:34:51,988
You killed Mink, you son of a bitch!

1170
01:34:53,267 --> 01:34:56,669
It was Mink, you son of a bitch.

1171
01:34:56,738 --> 01:35:01,608
It was Mink, and by God, I'll hear you say it.

1172
01:35:01,677 --> 01:35:04,111
Is this how you told Drop his story?

1173
01:35:06,383 --> 01:35:08,681
Come here, bum.

1174
01:35:12,456 --> 01:35:15,620
I am gonna send you to a deep, dark place,

1175
01:35:15,694 --> 01:35:18,492
and I am gonna have fun doing it.

1176
01:35:34,949 --> 01:35:36,918
Oof.

1177
01:35:36,986 --> 01:35:42,254
You son of a bitch! Son of a bitch!
You lousy son of a bitch!

1178
01:35:42,326 --> 01:35:46,092
If there's one thing I can't stand,
 it's a double-cross artist!

1179
01:35:48,566 --> 01:35:51,593
I had a theory about this son of a bitch!

1180
01:35:55,941 --> 01:36:00,845
Shut up, you lousy son of a bitch,
or I'll give you something to holler about!

1181
01:36:00,914 --> 01:36:04,043
Johnny, it's okay. The Dane made him do it.
 It's not important.

1182
01:36:04,118 --> 01:36:07,680
Then make him shut it!

1183
01:36:07,756 --> 01:36:11,624
And we do the same to Mink
 this very same night!

1184
01:36:11,693 --> 01:36:14,629
We can't double-cross Mink.
He wants to spill the whole setup.

1185
01:36:14,697 --> 01:36:18,327
- I've never let a son of a bitch walk.
- You've never crossed anyone.

1186
01:36:18,402 --> 01:36:21,929
4:00, my place. Mink's coming in on
 his own hook, so I promised him the money.

1187
01:36:22,005 --> 01:36:27,273
- Don't make me out to be a liar.

1188
01:36:29,782 --> 01:36:32,307
Look at this, kid.

1189
01:36:33,987 --> 01:36:36,922
Something I try to teach all my boys.

1190
01:36:46,502 --> 01:36:49,438
Always put one in the brain.

1191
01:37:11,398 --> 01:37:13,332
What's the rumpus?

1192
01:37:13,400 --> 01:37:16,928
I was just in the neighborhood
 feeling a little daffy.

1193
01:37:17,005 --> 01:37:19,303
- What are you doing?
- Walking.

1194
01:37:19,374 --> 01:37:21,639
Don't let on more than you have to.

1195
01:37:21,710 --> 01:37:23,644
In the rain.

1196
01:37:28,318 --> 01:37:30,253
Bernie's dead, isn't he?

1197
01:37:31,556 --> 01:37:34,650
- What makes you think that?
- That's no answer.

1198
01:37:39,398 --> 01:37:42,061
I can't tell you
anything yet.

1199
01:37:42,135 --> 01:37:45,070
No one really cares, do they?

1200
01:37:45,138 --> 01:37:50,270
- His friends didn't really like him.
 - He didn't like his friends.

1201
01:37:50,344 --> 01:37:53,576
You're someone to talk.
You're a son of a bitch, Tom.

1202
01:37:53,648 --> 01:37:56,584
You got me to tell you where he was,
and then you killed him.

1203
01:37:57,854 --> 01:37:59,879
I want to know why.

1204
01:37:59,956 --> 01:38:03,723
- What was in it for you?
- Nothing for me.

1205
01:38:08,166 --> 01:38:11,864
Giving up Bernie was the only way I could see
 to straighten things out for Leo.

1206
01:38:13,906 --> 01:38:16,842
I thought you said you didn't care about Leo.

1207
01:38:16,910 --> 01:38:20,573
I said we were through. It's not the same thing.

1208
01:38:20,647 --> 01:38:23,208
I don't understand. I don't care.

1209
01:38:23,284 --> 01:38:26,583
I don't care what reasons you had
 or you thought you had.

1210
01:38:26,654 --> 01:38:29,180
He's still alive.

1211
01:38:31,326 --> 01:38:33,420
You expect me to believe you?

1212
01:38:38,702 --> 01:38:40,636
No.

1213
01:38:43,942 --> 01:38:47,036
That's you all over, Tom.

1214
01:38:47,112 --> 01:38:49,547
A lie and no heart.

1215
01:39:07,536 --> 01:39:09,471
Oh--

1216
01:39:16,948 --> 01:39:19,042
It isn't easy, is it, Verna?

1217
01:39:34,736 --> 01:39:38,638
you even think about doing that,
 you gotta towel down.

1218
01:39:38,707 --> 01:39:44,169
So you towel down first with a hot towel,
 as hot as you can stand.

1219
01:39:44,246 --> 01:39:46,807
Put the razor in cold water, not hot,

1220
01:39:46,883 --> 01:39:49,613
because metal does what in cold?

1221
01:39:49,686 --> 01:39:54,056
- I don't know,Johnny.
 - That's why I'm telling you! It contracts.

1222
01:39:56,328 --> 01:40:00,196
That way you get
a first-class shave every time.

1223
01:40:00,265 --> 01:40:02,200
Okay,Johnny.

1224
01:40:04,838 --> 01:40:06,932
Ain't it the life though?

1225
01:40:10,544 --> 01:40:14,106
Hello, Sal. You can dangle.

1226
01:40:14,182 --> 01:40:18,988
Hello, Tom. You sure?
You don't look so hot.

1227
01:40:19,121 --> 01:40:20,952
I'm okay.

1228
01:40:23,593 --> 01:40:25,823
I'll drive him home.

1229
01:41:18,359 --> 01:41:21,192
Mr. Reagan, there were shots.

1230
01:41:21,262 --> 01:41:24,198
Go down to the drug store and call the police.

1231
01:41:25,901 --> 01:41:28,769
You'd better stay there
 till the officers arrive.

1232
01:41:29,839 --> 01:41:31,898
Will my cats be all right?

1233
01:41:31,974 --> 01:41:34,034
Yeah, they'll be fine.

1234
01:42:25,806 --> 01:42:28,832
I get it. You set me up.

1235
01:42:28,909 --> 01:42:31,936
Anything to avoid a little
 dirty work yourself, huh?

1236
01:42:34,015 --> 01:42:37,349
How'd you know he'd get it and not me?
 Or didn't you care?

1237
01:42:37,419 --> 01:42:39,910
I figured you'd come early looking for blood.

1238
01:42:39,989 --> 01:42:42,925
He wouldn't,
so you'd likely have the drop on him.

1239
01:42:44,561 --> 01:42:48,760
You're right.
The chump never knew what hit him.

1240
01:42:48,833 --> 01:42:52,292
But if you knew I'd come to kill you,
 how do you know I won't still?

1241
01:42:52,371 --> 01:42:55,363
There's nothing in it for you now.

1242
01:42:55,440 --> 01:42:58,376
With him dead, you and me
got nothing on each other.

1243
01:42:59,345 --> 01:43:01,871
- Let me have the gun.
- Why?

1244
01:43:01,949 --> 01:43:04,383
Pin this on the Dane.

1245
01:43:04,451 --> 01:43:07,444
Neither of us want him
walking around after this.

1246
01:43:07,522 --> 01:43:11,288
The cops'll be Leo's now. They won't care
 what they hang the Dane for.

1247
01:43:11,359 --> 01:43:13,294
I guess that's true,

1248
01:43:13,362 --> 01:43:17,732
if you don't mind keeping the gun
 that killed Caspar and Mink.

1249
01:43:18,835 --> 01:43:21,235
Why did Mink shoot Rug anyway?

1250
01:43:21,305 --> 01:43:23,297
I don't know.
It was just a mix-up.

1251
01:43:23,374 --> 01:43:25,842
Here.

1252
01:43:28,614 --> 01:43:32,380
- So you're gonna say the Dane did this?
 - Sure.

1253
01:43:32,451 --> 01:43:35,250
Mink thought Rug was tailing him.

1254
01:43:35,322 --> 01:43:37,882
You know Mink. Hysterical.
Skin full of hop, head full of boogeymen.

1255
01:43:37,958 --> 01:43:42,521
Comes home crying one day,
 saying he had to pop one of the Dane's spies.

1256
01:43:42,597 --> 01:43:46,193
Rug was tailing Verna, not Mink.
Mink just happened to be with her.

1257
01:43:46,268 --> 01:43:48,202
Funny, ain't it?

1258
01:43:48,270 --> 01:43:51,502
Mink was terrified the Dane'd find out
 me and him were jungled up together.

1259
01:43:51,574 --> 01:43:54,567
I bet you kept him worried about that
 to keep him under your thumb.

1260
01:43:54,645 --> 01:43:57,079
Yeah, so what?
Scratch, huh?

1261
01:43:57,147 --> 01:43:59,776
A little bonus.

1262
01:43:59,851 --> 01:44:03,252
- Why did Mink take Rug's hair?
 - Beats me. The kid was dizzy.

1263
01:44:03,321 --> 01:44:07,520
Fifty-fifty on the dough? Or maybe
 I should get more, since I did the deed.

1264
01:44:10,030 --> 01:44:11,931
Okay, you keep it.
 I want you to have it.

1265
01:44:18,966 --> 01:44:23,234
Bernie...
we can't pin this on the Dane.

1266
01:44:24,076 --> 01:44:25,019
 Why not?

1267
01:44:26,002 --> 01:44:29,062
 Because the Dane's already dead
halfway across town.

1268
01:44:29,800 --> 01:44:32,859
- What the hell are you talking about?
- Eddie Dane is dead.

1269
01:44:33,256 --> 01:44:34,438
It's gotta be you.

1270
01:44:36,597 --> 01:44:38,420
I mean, it was your gun.

1271
01:44:40,718 --> 01:44:44,625
What is this?
What the hell are you talking about?

1272
01:44:46,173 --> 01:44:47,173
You--

1273
01:44:48,476 --> 01:44:51,440
You took my gun.
It's just your word against mine.

1274
01:44:55,139 --> 01:44:56,513
Not necessarily.

1275
01:44:58,554 --> 01:45:00,094
Are you crazy?

1276
01:45:00,314 --> 01:45:03,659
We're square. You said it yourself.
We got nothing on each other.

1277
01:45:04,561 --> 01:45:05,561
Yep.

1278
01:45:06,998 --> 01:45:10,245
So what's in it for you?
There's no angle.

1279
01:45:10,345 --> 01:45:12,986
You can't just shoot me like that.

1280
01:45:17,844 --> 01:45:20,861
Jesus Christ... it don't make sense.

1281
01:45:23,584 --> 01:45:25,518
Tommy--

1282
01:45:27,389 --> 01:45:29,217
Tommy!

1283
01:45:31,727 --> 01:45:32,912
Look in your heart.

1284
01:45:35,524 --> 01:45:37,790
- Look in your heart.
- What heart?

1285
01:46:24,022 --> 01:46:26,116
Tad? It's Tom.

1286
01:46:27,093 --> 01:46:28,679
Tell Lazarre I got his money.

1287
01:46:29,800 --> 01:46:31,518
Yeah, all of it.

1288
01:46:32,249 --> 01:46:34,434
I wanna place a bet on tonight's fight.

1289
01:46:39,350 --> 01:46:41,297
- They set you up downstairs?
- How's that?

1290
01:46:41,366 --> 01:46:42,822
A little hooch, whatever?

1291
01:46:44,050 --> 01:46:46,997
Thanks for coming, Tom.
 Leo's real anxious to see you.

1292
01:46:47,066 --> 01:46:49,168
Yeah, I happened to be near.

1293
01:46:51,490 --> 01:46:54,735
Well, uh,
actually this might not be  the best time.

1294
01:46:54,808 --> 01:46:57,756
- Who's he got in there?
- O'Doole and the mayor.

1295
01:46:58,358 --> 01:46:59,263
I'll try again.

1296
01:46:59,263 --> 01:47:01,558
They're planting the sheeny tomorrow.
You could stop by.

1297
01:47:31,710 --> 01:47:34,067
- Big turnout.
- Drop dead.

1298
01:47:35,596 --> 01:47:37,698
She's under a lot of strain.

1299
01:47:37,775 --> 01:47:40,048
Yeah, well...
at least she didn't hit me.

1300
01:47:42,543 --> 01:47:44,144
Glad you came, Tommy.

1301
01:47:44,813 --> 01:47:47,308
- I guess, uh-- Huh?
- She's taking the car.

1302
01:47:53,126 --> 01:47:55,693
- I guess we're walkin'.
- Guess we are.

1303
01:48:01,296 --> 01:48:03,163
We're, uh--
We're getting married.

1304
01:48:06,397 --> 01:48:07,749
Congratulations.

1305
01:48:08,756 --> 01:48:13,768
Funny thing is, she asked me to tie the knot.
I guess you're not supposed to say that.

1306
01:48:13,868 --> 01:48:16,077
- It doesn't matter. Congratulations.
- Thanks.

1307
01:48:18,464 --> 01:48:21,048
Hell, Tom, why didn't you tell me
 what you were up to?

1308
01:48:21,148 --> 01:48:22,787
I thought you'd really gone over.

1309
01:48:23,958 --> 01:48:26,202
Not that I didn't deserve it,
but you could've told me.

1310
01:48:27,512 --> 01:48:29,629
Telling you would only
have queered things if it--

1311
01:48:31,161 --> 01:48:32,611
There just wasn't any point.

1312
01:48:34,470 --> 01:48:35,709
I can see that.

1313
01:48:37,419 --> 01:48:39,274
It was a smart play all around.

1314
01:48:40,742 --> 01:48:43,600
I guess... you know I'm grateful.

1315
01:48:43,727 --> 01:48:44,956
No need.

1316
01:48:47,957 --> 01:48:50,344
Heh! I guess you picked that fight with me...

1317
01:48:50,444 --> 01:48:53,260
just to check yourself in with Caspar.

1318
01:48:53,688 --> 01:48:57,191
I don't know. Do you always
 know why you do things, Leo?

1319
01:48:57,547 --> 01:48:58,901
Sure I do.

1320
01:49:01,839 --> 01:49:04,189
- It was a smart play.
- Fine.

1321
01:49:07,709 --> 01:49:10,766
Jesus, Tom, I'd do anything
 if you'd work for me again.

1322
01:49:11,378 --> 01:49:14,526
I know I've made some bonehead plays,
 I know I can be pigheaded sometimes.

1323
01:49:14,669 --> 01:49:16,084
But, damn it, so can you.

1324
01:49:17,601 --> 01:49:20,985
I need you.
Things can be the way they were.

1325
01:49:21,973 --> 01:49:23,802
I know it. I just know it.

1326
01:49:25,359 --> 01:49:28,783
As for you and Verna,
well... I understand.

1327
01:49:28,883 --> 01:49:30,086
You're both young.

1328
01:49:32,493 --> 01:49:34,058
Damn it, Tom, I forgive you.

1329
01:49:34,158 --> 01:49:36,222
I didn't ask for that, and I don't want it.

1330
01:49:44,000 --> 01:49:44,956
Good-bye, Leo.


